The paper proposes a novel approach for predicting the motion of pedestrians, which involves the use of Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) and Info-GAN. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) or Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves the prediction of multi-modal distributions, which could also place it in the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. The use of GANs for predicting pedestrian trajectories also suggests that the paper could belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the analysis of experiments on real and synthetic data, which could also place it in the Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) sub-category.
